China Sells 3-Year Yuan Bonds in Hong Kong at 0.6 Percent, Tsang Says

-- B y   S a n d y   H e n d r y
-- 
2011-08-17T03:28:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/china-sells-3-year-yuan-bonds-in-hong-kong-at-0-6-percent-tsang-says.html
China’s Ministry of Finance sold
three-year yuan bonds in  Hong Kong  at 0.6 percent after
receiving “satisfactory” demand from institutional investors,
Hong Kong Financial Secretary John Tsang said.  The ministry is also selling five-, seven- and 10-year
bonds to finance companies in the city and two-year debt to
individuals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sandy Hendry in Hong Kong at 
 shendry@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandy Hendry at 
 shendry@bloomberg.net  